# Documentation Guidelines

## Philosophy
* Documentation must be concise and easy to read.
* Do not go overboard trying to sound smart or sophisticated. Simple, direct information is required.
* Prioritize readability and ease of understanding, even at the expense of grammatical correctness.

## Scope & Technical Depth
* Focus on the scope and the *why* behind how things are done.
* Avoid delving into deep technical details. Highly technical details change often, leaving docs outdated and causing confusion. Only include technical specifics if they are critical and unlikely to change.

## Avoid Redundancy
* Do not explain the same mechanism in multiple places.
* Having redundant explanations under different scopes is dangerous because it requires remembering to update all instances when changes occur. Keep a single source of truth.
